## 🚨 Mandatory Check Declaration for AI Executing Start-Task

**CRITICAL**: When the AI executes the start-task flow, it **MUST** output check declarations at each phase to avoid skipping important steps due to task-oriented thinking.

### Phase 1: After Reading Jira Ticket

**Required check declaration**:

```
⚠️ Start-Task Phase 1 Check:

📋 Ticket info has been read:
   Ticket: {TICKET}
   Title: {SUMMARY}
   Type: {ISSUE_TYPE}

🔍 RD suggestion check result:
   [✓] Checked Description for "for AI" / "to AI" markers
   [✓] Checked Comments for "AI suggestion" markers
   Result: {FOUND / NOT_FOUND}

🎯 Initial development plan:
   1. {STEP_1}
   2. {STEP_2}
   ...

❓ Please confirm whether this development plan is correct?
```

**Phase completion condition**: User confirms the development plan

---

### Phase 2: After Development Complete

**Required check declaration**:

```
⚠️ Start-Task Phase 2 Check:

📋 Development completion check:
   [✓] All development steps completed
   [✓] Development plan saved to Git notes
   [✓] Changed files: {FILES_CHANGED}

📝 Summary of this modification:
   - Added: {NEW_FILES}
   - Modified: {MODIFIED_FILES}
   - Deleted: {DELETED_FILES}

❓ Please confirm whether the modifications are correct? The cr command will be executed after confirmation.
```

**Phase completion condition**: User confirms modification content

---

### Phase 3: After MR Created

**Required check declaration**:

```
⚠️ Start-Task Phase 3 Check:

📋 MR creation check:
   [✓] MR Description contains development plan
   [✓] MR Description contains problem analysis (if Bug)
   [✓] AI label added
   [✓] Git notes saved

✅ MR created successfully: {MR_LINK}
```

**Phase completion condition**: MR successfully created

---

### Strict Enforcement Rules

**CRITICAL**: If the AI proceeds to the next step without outputting the above check declarations, it is a **serious violation**.

| Phase | Check item | Violation consequence |
|---|---|---|
| Phase 1 | Starting development without showing development plan | Stop immediately, re-show plan |
| Phase 2 | Executing cr without showing modification summary | Stop immediately, re-show summary |
| Phase 3 | MR missing development plan or AI label | Update MR to add missing content |

